    {
      "Text": "Security update for the Linux Kernel (Live Patch 14 for SLE 12 SP3)",
      "Title": "Topic",
      "Type": "Summary"
    },
    {
      "Text": "This update for the Linux Kernel 4.4.138-94_39 fixes one issue.\n\nThe following security issue was fixed:\n\n- CVE-2018-3646: Local attackers in virtualized guest systems could use speculative code patterns on hyperthreaded processors to read data present in the L1 Datacache used by other hyperthreads on the same CPU core, potentially leaking sensitive data, even from other virtual machines or the host system (bsc#1099306).\n",
      "Title": "Details",
      "Type": "General"
    },
